S|# YVON Agent Engine — Core Architecture & Build Plan (v1)|> The core engine. Runs many agents and many sessions in parallel, with graph mem, // > the Hermes learning loop + MCP, verification, and self-improvement. Triple-pass rv // > (**[crit]** = changed by the critique pass). Supersedes WAR_ROOM_FIX_PLAN; that plan's // > workstreams are absorbed as engine components below.
S|The hard architectural truth (read first)|Hermes is a persistent **Python** service. Vercel serverless **cannot** host it, run its MCP server, or hold long-running multi-ses state (60s functions, no persistence). To get the Hermes engine + MCP + reliable parallel sessions, the topology becomes: // ``` // ┌────────────┐    SSE/HTTP    ┌────────────────────────┐   MCP    ┌──────────────────┐ // │ Next.js UI │ ◄────────────► │  Orchestrator Worker   │ ◄──────► │ Hermes sidecar   │ // │ (Vercel)   │   enqueue/     │  (persistent Node svc) │
S|PART A — Session & Concurrency Engine  ⟵ build FIRST [crit]|*The thing you said matters most: many sessions in parallel without breaking each other.* // - **ses object.** Every War Room run = an isolated `ses { id, ventureSlug, repoMode, localRepoPath, memoryNamespace, cache, eventBus, createdAt }`. Nothing shared between sessions except read-only global config. // - **Per-ses caches.** The tree/cnt caches (Part E) live **inside the ses**, never module-global — keyed by `(sessionId, localRepoPath, path)`, with write-invalidation + TTL. Eliminates cross-s
S|PART B — Hermes Sidecar (engine + MCP + learning loop)|- **Stand up Hermes** as a container from the repo (it's MIT, Python). Configure it headless (no Telegram/Discord) exposing only its **MCP server** (`mcp_serve.py` / `hermes_tools_mcp_server.py`). // - **MCP client in the orchestrator.** Add an MCP client so all 13 agents can call Hermes tools (mem, skill, subagent, search) during their work. // - **Learning loop, connected to every agt.** Use Hermes `agt/memory_manager.py` + mem plugins as the experience store. After each **verified** task (Par
S|PART C — Memory Fabric (graph + learned + skills, unified)|*Three mem types, one recall interface every agt uses.* // 1. **Graph mem (NEW agt tool).** Server-side reader over `graphify-out/graph.json` (+ code-rv graph) exposed as a `GraphQuery` tool: "what depends on X", "callers of Y", "impact radius of editing Z". Agents query the graph **before** editing → fewer half-applied refactors (the 7-regression bug). *(Note: the `graphify` CLI paths in package.json are Windows-only; runtime querying reads `graph.json` directly in Node — no CLI dependency [cri
S|PART D — Correctness & Verification Engine|- **Build gate** per stack (Flutter `flutter analyze`, TS `tsc`, etc.): baseline-diff catches regressions, feeds exact `file:line` back to the right agt, **cap 3 rounds**, blocks false "fixed." (Already proven the need: 7 agt-introduced errors.) // - **Graph-aware editing:** before a fix, agt queries impact radius (Part C1) → updates all dependents → re-verify. // - **Fail-closed QA** (already shipped) + the build gate = truthful "VERIFIED / N ERRORS REMAIN." // - **Spaced-path read/bash reliabi
S|PART E — Efficiency Engine|- **Dedup tree exploration:** map repo once per ses (Part A cache), serve Glob/Grep from it, give agents the complete subtree. // - **Dedup file reads:** cache contents, forward analyzer-read files into downstream briefs so fixers/QA never re-read. // - **Prompt caching** (already hardened: single trailing breakpoint).
S|PART F — Agentic Flow Redesign|*Per ses, using the pulled `subagent-driven-dev` skill:* // ``` // PLAN (Marcus) → DELEGATE (subagents per task, parallel where independent) //    → EXECUTE (specialist + recall + graph) → VERIFY (build gate, ≤3 rounds) //    → LEARN (Hermes loop captures verified outcome) → SYNTHESIZE (Marcus, truthful) // ``` // - **Multi-agt parallel within a ses** (independent tasks) + **multi-ses parallel across** (Part A). // - Continuation/resume from history (fix the broken autoApprove path; ctx + cards 
S|PART G — Reasoning|- Always-on **thinking toggle** + targeted retry-without-thinking fallback. Honest trade-off: depth vs latency.
S|PART H — Rollout, Ops, Fallback|### LOCKED: Foundation first, PAUSE before Hermes. // Build and prove the foundation natively, then stop and rv before standing up the Python sidecar/MCP/learning-loop. // **FOUNDATION (now — Parts A, E, C-graph, D):** // - **A — ses & concurrency engine**, in sub-steps: //   - **A1** Introduce the `ses` abstraction + per-ses caches/isolation **inside the current Next.js pl** (behind a flag). Multi-ses-safe immediately, no new infra. ⟵ first concrete step //   - **A2** Extract the orchestrator i
S|Already shipped (this session, local)|Synthesis verification · cache_control fix · fail-closed QA · spaced-path regex · agt-work DB persistence (cards restore) · Hermes skill packs pulled + weekly sync + tracking docs. These become components D/E/C of the engine.
S|Triple-pass critique → fixes folded in|- Build sessions/concurrency FIRST (it's the core requirement) and load-test it before anything rides on it. // - Everything behind flags + graceful fallback to the current pl — never break the working path. // - Per-ses caches (not module-global) to guarantee no cross-ses leakage. // - Honest hosting reality (Python sidecar + worker; Vercel can't host them) surfaced as the one dec to confirm. // - Graph querying reads `graph.json` in Node (no Windows CLI dependency). // - Learning capture only 
